    "body": "I am developing a package `py-yt` that declares this dependency:\n\n``` Python\n    depends_on(\"mercurial\", type=\"build\")\n```\n\nand yet fails with this error:\n\n```\n$ spack -k fetch py-yt\n==> Warning: You asked for --insecure. Will NOT check SSL certificates.\n==> Trying to fetch from file:///home/eschnett/src/spack-yt/var/spack/cache/py-yt/py-yt-3.3.1.tar.gz\ncurl: (37) Couldn't open file /home/eschnett/src/spack-yt/var/spack/cache/py-yt/py-yt-3.3.1.tar.gz\n==> Fetching from file:///home/eschnett/src/spack-yt/var/spack/cache/py-yt/py-yt-3.3.1.tar.gz failed.\n==> Trying to clone Mercurial repository:\n  https://bitbucket.org/yt_analysis/yt\n==> Error: spack requires hg.  Make sure it is in your path.\n```\n\nAny pointers towards correcting the `mercurial` package to properly provide the `hg` executable are appreciated.\n",
